column5: Well they're were reports all over the local radio station this morning about flooding and very dangerous conditions here in dover, Through the night and this morning. Again the main intersection coming into dover at the cross roads was all blocked off as the water levels had yet again reached way up by main. I decided to take a drive down this morning and shoot this video footage.  Great big slabs of ice all over the roads and side walk.  The wind is just incredible and the whole pier is just one thick blanket of ice.  If you watch on the video you will see the end of the peir is all burried under one big huge chunk of ice. Never seen that before.  Still crazy high gusts of winds here in dover which started up around 3.00am here. Anyway enjoy the video.
Man, you just don't mess with Mother Nature.
Wow!! Thanks for the video  Enough winter already!!!!!!!!!!!  Al Spoonmaster lures
that was a pretty cool video!  thanks for sharing!  Cheers!
your voice is different than I expected........Mea West'y

That was quite the day, I was around Nanticoke yesterday and could not help but get close to the action. That was the worst I have seen the lake in many years, great footage on the video, it was really something to see!!
Glad you all enjoyed the video & thanx for watching.
